The synthesis phase should organize case studies by type of breakdown
(revolutionary, institutional collapse, totalitarian destruction, gradual
erosion) and identify common causal mechanisms across cases. Special attention
should be paid to Arendt's conceptual framework for understanding tradition
breakdown through revolution and totalitarianism, as this provides a bridge
between empirical cases and theoretical analysis. The contrast between Weimar
and post-WWII German democracy offers particularly valuable insights into
conditions for tradition resilience versus failure.

