  RELEVANCE: Addresses fundamental question of whether tradition-based rationality is coherent or self-defeating—crucial for understanding when traditions genuinely fail versus when they are merely criticized from external standpoints. Seipel's defense suggests that traditions fail when they lose capacity for internal criticism and problem-solving, not simply when they maintain particular commitments.

