  substantive positive visions of living well, not merely resisting colonialism.

  RELEVANCE: Illuminates fundamental incompatibility between certain Western
  philosophical frameworks (including ostensibly critical ones) and Indigenous
  traditions. Shows how even well-intentioned Western theories can perpetuate
  tradition destruction by imposing categories (purely negative normativity,
  historical constructivism) that are alien to Indigenous thought. Relevant for
  understanding epistemic violence as mode of tradition breakdown—not just
  physical destruction but conceptual frameworks that make tradition unintelligible
  or irrational.

  POSITION: Indigenous philosophy perspective; critical of both liberal and
  critical theory frameworks for inadequately engaging Indigenous thought on
  its own terms.
  },
  keywords = {indigenous-thought, critical-theory, epistemology, Medium}
}

@article{george2023modernity,
